# CODEOWNERS — auto-assigned reviewers per path.
# Syntax: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Replace @OWNER with your handle or team (e.g. @me, @my-org/maintainers).
# A template ships ONE placeholder owner on purpose: branch protection that
# requires code-owner review blocks every PR if a listed owner/team doesn't
# exist in your org. Add specialised teams (security, devops, product) once they do.

# Default owners (catch-all).
*                               @OWNER

# Security-sensitive areas — point at a security team once you have one.
src/security/                   @OWNER
src/api/Api.hpp                 @OWNER

# Infrastructure.
docker/                         @OWNER
helm/                           @OWNER
.gitlab-ci.yml                  @OWNER
.github/                        @OWNER

# Docs / API contract.
docs/openapi.yaml               @OWNER
